inn1.comm: good length angling across the right-hander from over the wicket, Azhar stays back and steers the ball towards third man
full and straight from Boult, at 127kph, driven back at the bowler and he fields in his follow through
pushed towards short midwicket for a single, Guptill mis-fielded that
full on the pads, flicked deftly but can't beat square leg
slants across the right-hander this time and the batsmen lets it go
a length ball just outside off, punched off the back foot to point
good length outside off stump, left alone by the batsman
short of a length on straighter line, Shehzad stays back and works the ball off his hips down to fine leg
strides forward to a fuller ball, 137 kph that is, and punches to point
a fuller length on off and middle stump at 140 kph, the batsman moves across his stumps and turns the ball towards square leg
gets squared up as he defends a good length ball that pitched off and middle and straightens a touch
can't bowl that line with such short straight boundaries, Shehzad glances off his hips at fine leg has no chance
strays down leg side, first extra of the innings
a fuller ball slants across Azhar and comes into the right-hander a little, he gets on the front foot and punches towards cover
that's not short enough to pull but Azhar tries to do so from just outside off stump, he gets a bottom edge that bounces through to Ronchi
good length outside off, he strides forward and lets it go
gets on the front foot and shoulders arms again as Boult goes wide outside off from over the wicket
a fuller ball outside off, driven off the front foot to the fielder at cover
Azhar moves forward and towards the off side, but then has to check his shot as Boult moves the ball away from the right hander and squares the batsman up, beaten
good length on a wicket to wicket line, played from the crease towards mid on
140 kph, short ball, the first one of the day, Shehzad shapes to pull but does not go through with the shot as the ball whizzes past his right shoulder
defended from the crease on the off side
ooh he should have put that away! A half-volley with width outside off stump, Shehzad leans into a flowing drive but can't beat the man at point
pulls his length back a touch on a good line outside off, the batsman lets it go this time
139 kph, a full ball outside off, driven through extra cover, good to see McCullum chase after this line he usually does, hauls it in just beyond the inner circle
good length, pitching in line with the stumps and slanting across, the batsman lets it pass
short and wide outside off, hit me please! Shehzad stays back and cuts the ball hard and through the gap at point this time
Boult goes around the wicket and angles into the right-hander, a fuller length, nudged towards square leg
a good length outside off, Azhar stays back and cuts the ball down to third man

what a sharp catch that is! Guptill at short midwicket! Shehzad swivelled on the back foot and pulled really well, making clean contact. The only thing he did wrong was hit it in the air towards short midwicket, where Guptill was waiting, crouched low. He took it so smoothly at shin height, though that ball was travelling quickly
cracked it first ball! It was short and wide from Boult, angling across the right-hander, Hafeez stayed back and flayed it over the fielder at point with a fierce cut shot

caught at second slip! The length was good and the line just outside off stump was great. The delivery just held its line a touch and Azhar's hard drive off the front foot resulted in a thick edge straight to Guptill once again, such safe hands
stays back and tucks a good length ball towards wide mid on
good length outside off, punched off the back foot to point
138 kph, just short of a length outside off, really good bounce through to Ronchi after Babar is beaten on the back foot punch through cover
this time he makes contact, moving back and punching the short of a length ball that is close to him through cover
a fuller ball outside off this time, Babar hits it off the front foot through cover with another drive
good length angling into the right-hander from around the wicket, Hafeez stays in his crease and defends

edged and just wide of the solitary slip, who dived full length to his right. Corey Anderson that was. The batsman pushed hard away from his body, with a slightly open face. think McCullum had only one slip because Boult is bowling around the wicket
a fuller ball, punched to mid on
nudged into the off side, Hafeez calls poorly from the striker's end and Babar has to hurry back, he's lucky the throw did not hit
steered off the back foot to short third man
a high full toss, the batsman is surprised a touch and defends on the off side, a free hit coming up
that's in the stands beyond long on, the length was too full - Boult missing the yorker - and Hafeez gets under it and lofts powerfully back past the bowler. Cleared his front foot and swung hard.
good length, played towards midwicket
defended on the off side
banged in short outside off stump, that's too high
drives with hard hands away from his body at a full ball outside off, the outside edge goes to third man
good length and on middle and off, 141 kph, Hafeez gets behind the line and defends
short ball, it hurries on to Hafeez who manages to swivel and pull through square leg
good length on off once again, Hafeez gets on the front foot and defends
a full ball bends back into the right-hander, Babar gets on the front foot and swipes at the ball, hitting against the angle through point
the ball jags back into the right-hander, cramping Hafeez for room in his crease and rushing the batsman, Hafeez gets hit on the thigh as he tries to defend
this time Hafeez swivels in time to hit the ball with the incoming angle behind square, not timed well though

edged and once again it is wide of the sole slip, Anderson leaping to his right with his right hand at full stretch, that's the second time one has gone there ...Babar drove hard at a full ball outside off

driven smoothly off the front foot through extra cover this time and McCullum is in hot pursuit ... he dives full length again, like he did when he aggravated his back injury! This time he can't prevent the four
fuller ball, defended to the bowler
played with soft hands close on the off side for a single
140 kph, driven fluently off the front foot to mid-off
full ball outside off, driven off the front foot through cover
driven off the front foot through extra cover, McCullum chases again, not timed well so he races that down
139 kph, a full ball outside off, driven to mid-off
turned off the hips towards square leg for a single
good length across the right hander from over the wicket, defended from the crease
a full ball on a straight line, Babar gets on the front foot and lofts the ball with the movement into him over midwicket, in the air but well timed
stays back this time and defends a good length ball with an open face on the off side
shot! The ball was full on off and middle, Hafeez got on to the front foot and drove with a perfectly straight bat, splitting the gap between the stumps and the non-striker
shot again! anderson drags his length back and bowls too short, Hafeez swivels on the front foot and pulls to the backward square leg boundary
reverts to a good length outside off, Hafeez moves forward and shoulder arms
the boundaries are flowing! Babar this time, getting on to the front foot and driving a full ball to the left of the diving fielder at mid-on, the 50 partnership is up
defended on the back foot on the off side
short of a length and straight, stays back and plays the ball in front of square leg
he tried to pull a short ball but top edged it in the air, Ronchi runs forward and to his left, towards the leg slip region, but can;'t get to it in time
left alone outside off stump
short ball once again, the batsman swivels and pulls to deep square leg
pushed off the front foot towards cover point
tucked off the pads towards square leg

shot! Those short straight boundaries are cleared easily even though the bat turned in his hand and he ended up slicing it. The batsman charged the bowler and lofted through the line, clearing the long off fielder
pushed to long on for a single
worked off the back foot towards square leg
shorter length and the batsman pulls to deep square leg
141 kph right away, length ball on middle and leg, played off the back foot towards square leg
fiery, right in the blockhole, dug out on the off side
good length and straight at 145 kph, gets behind the line and blocks it
so athletic from Mlilne! Leaps to his right in his follow through to field the ball and throws back towards the batsman, he misses the stumps through
tucked off the hips through square leg for a single
146 kph, Milne working up a brisk pace, short of a length and straight, tucked off the hips through square leg
goes back and pulls through the leg side
short of a length again, the batsman is able to go back in his crease and pull to deep midwicket
played off the pads towards square leg
stays in his crease and pushes the good length ball to long on
goes back and across to pull, mis-times it this time though to square leg
fuller length on the pads, turned through square leg
short ball, pulled to deep square leg
cut off the back foot through point
defended off the back foot on the off side
shot! Gets on the front foot to a full ball and lofts cleanly through the line, making great contact and sending it racing to the long off boundary
short ball and the batsman swivels and pulls through midwicket to bring up the 100 for Pakistan
great improvisation from Hafeez, the line was down leg side so the batsman went across his crease, got down low and paddled it to the fine leg boundary
turned off the pads towards long leg for a single
strays down leg side, tries to turn it off the pads but can't make contact
cut off the back foot but can't beat point
played back to the bowler on the front foot, four dot balls to finish the over
good length and straight at 145 kph, the batsman gets behind the line and blocks
defended on the front foot on the off side
full and straight from Milne, Hafeez gets on the front foot and blocks
tucked off the hips through square leg for a single
a full ball on off and middle stump, driven on the front foot to mid off
that was rapid, a short ball at 147 kph, the batsman tries to cut but is beaten for pace
defended on the front foot
played towards midwicket
charges down the pitch and lofts the ball powerfully over long on, that's a long long way back in the stands and he brings up his 50 off 40 balls, superb innings
cut off the back foot but can't beat backward point
pushed down the ground for a single to long on
tucked off the pads towards square leg
143 kph, good length around off stump, defended on the front foot
a full ball on a straight line, defended on the off side
short ball and he's nailed that, pulling it hard and far over the long deep midwicket boundary
mis-times the pull this time to midwicket
played off the back foot towards point
Milne tries to end the over with a fiery bouncer that soars over the keeper's head, Ronchi had no chance
played off the back foot towards cover
strays down leg side, that's a wide
steps out of his crease and swings hard, he isn't to the pitch of the ball but on these short straight boundaries that does not matter too much
turned off the pads through square leg
pushed off the front foot to long on
steps out and tees off again, Babar this time, charging the spinner and slamming him over long off
steps out of his crease and clears the short long-on boundary with a powerful swing
a misfield at mid off! Babar goes to his half century with a straight drive along the groudn that really should have been stopped
played from the crease towards point
short of a length outside off, cut off the back foot towards deep point
tries to cut hard through point, but gets an edge towards third man
played off the back foot to point
short of a length outside off stump, cut off the back foot towards third man
short ball, the batsman swivels and pulls towards deep square
strays wide down leg side, the batsman sweeps and gets a tickle on it past the keeper, the fielder runs to his right from fine leg and dives to save the four - Henry that was
steps out and outside leg stump to play the ball towards cover
gets down on one knee and sweeps to deep square leg
goes back and across to pull the ball to deep square leg
played off the back foot in front of point
the slog sweep and he has holed out to deep backward square leg! Santner pitched outside leg stump, Hafeez got down on one knee and swung hard, top edging it straight to Milne on the boundary!
140 kph, a fast and fiery bouncer, the batsman ducks under it
another short ball, too high this time, 145 kph, the batsman lets it go outside off
shot! Babar stays balanced as he comes forward and drives a full ball through extra cover
tucked off the pads behind square leg
driven from the crease to cover
driven uppishly but wide of the fielder diving to his left at mid-on, McCullum bounces up and chases but his dive can't save the boundary
good length outside off stump, played from the crease into the covers
driven on the front foot to mid off
short ball outside leg from around the wicket, pulled off the back foot towards deep midwicket where Anderson runs to his left and lets it go through his legs! That was embarassing!
pushed off the front foot towards mid off
goes back and pulls the ball in front of square leg, Anderson runs in to field and gets a cheer from the crowd after doing it right this time
goes back and cuts the ball through point
goes back and pulls the ball to mid on, didn't have space to play the shot
shot! Mid-on is in the circle so Babar simply stands his ground and plays the lofted drive, hitting through the line to clear the infield
a fuller ball on the pads, he leans forward and clips it through square leg
147 kph, a good length around off stump, played from the crease to mid off
full ball homing in on off stump at 145 kph, played off the front foot towards point
punched on the up to mid off
a sensational delivery, too good for the batsman to edge, 149 kph on a good length just outside off and holding its line, Malik was squared up and beaten as he tried to defend
cut off the back foot to point
played back to the bowler
short ball, Malik goes back and pulls the ball straight past the bowler, mid-on dives to his left but can't cut off the shot

shot! Malik charges the spinner, getting to the pitch of the ball, and once he gets into that position it is so easy to clear the long on boundary with a swing of the arms, very short boundary in that direction
nudged gently through square leg and they run hard for two
punched off the back foot towards cover
a full ball outside off, Malik stays back and steers to third man
Santner fails to pick up the ball cleanly at deep point after Babar cuts, but no harm done for NZ
dabbed off the back foot towards backward point where Guptill dives to his left and fields
that's so wide outside off, Boult losing his lines with a high full toss
goes back and dabs the ball behind point this time
136kph, short ball angles across the right-hander and beats him on the pull
Guptill is fielding like a marvel today, diving to his right at point and cutting off a fierce cut shot. That nearly carried to him too
played with an open face off the back foot behind point
slower one outside off, cut off the back foot to point
shorter ball, Babar ducks and Ronchi fumbles a difficult take
played off the back foot through cover point
full and straight, driven off the front foot to long on
short ball, no deep midwicket, four. The batsman had so much time to rock back and pull hard
that's not short enough or wide enough outside off to cut, Malik tries but is beaten
steered to third man for a single
short of a length pitching outside leg, pulled through square leg
a fuller length rather wide outside off, Malik can't connect with his swipe, he looks at Bowden, who lets the wide call pass

did Malik know there was a fielder at a wide slip? He went back into his crease and dabbed the ball late. Anderson saw the ball flying quickly and low to his left but could not reach it. He got up quickly though to chase the ball down towars third man
steps forward and pulls a length ball hard and into the gap on the deep midwicket boundary
the short ball sits up outside off stump and Babar puts it away to deep midwicket with a pull off the back foot
glanced off the pads to fine leg for a single
pushed from the crease, he was aiming to go straight but the outside edge went towards point
a length ball outside off, he goes deep and cuts through point
dabbed off the back foot but can't beat short third man
cut off the back foot to deep point

caught behind! Boult makes a vital breakthrough for NZ, Malik loves the cut and he tried to flay the ball behind point. Boult's length was good from over the wicket and his line angling across the right-hander was not wide enough, there was good bounce too. Ronchi took an easy catch
stays in his crease and plays the ball behind point
shot! Such timing from Sarfraz second ball ... he leans forward and plays a lovely square drive through point

edged between the keeper and a wide first slip for four! Sarfraz wafts away from his body at a good length ball slanting across him and gets a thick nick. Ronchi dived to his right but could not reach it. Boult has watched three edges not go to hand today
played to backward point
defended on the off side from the crease
punched off the back foot to mid off for a single, the calling between the wickets is urgent
a bit of extra bounce from a good length outside off beats the poke off the front foot
pushed towards short midwicket from the crease
played to long on for a single
full and straight, driven firmly along the ground to long on
a slower ball, the batsman pushes forward but then checks his shot to ensure he does not play too early, Guptill cuts off the shot at short midwicket
Henry returns and bowls a short ball that is too high
driven to mid off
short of a length and straight, the batsman punches with a straight bat towards mid-on, who runs to his left and fields
cut off the back foot but can't get the ball past the man at backward point

he's cut the ball straight to point and Babar is so disappointed as he walks off! The ball was short of a length and there was width for the cut too, he just executed the placement poorly, hitting it straight to the fielder. Pakistan lose both set batsmen.
137 kph, good length outside off, left alone by Rizwan
pushed from the crease towards extra cover for a single
nudged off the pads towards midwicket for a quick single
pushed towards long on for a single
defended on the front foot to cover
cut off the back foot, can't beat point, New Zealand pulling this back nicely now
Milne runs to his left from long on and dives to ry and save the boundary, Rizwan had driven that off the front foot so fluently, Milne just about saves it
that nearly carried to backward point! The batsman stayed back and opened the face o run the ball to third man but ended up playing it uppishly just short of Williamson
tucked off the pads, from around off stump, through square leg
short of a length on the hips, glanced off the back foot behind square for a hard-run two
pushed off the front foot towards point
a full ball on the pads, flicked towards deep square leg
banged in short and the batsmen ducks under it
steps out of his crease to nudge the short of a length ball on the leg side, the ball lobs up gently off the edge but falls short of the bowler
that looked quicker than 137 kph, another short ball that the batsman leaves
pitches short and the batsman drags the ball from a line outside off stump through square leg with a pull shot
pushed off the front foot towards the bowler
gets an outside edge towards point as he tried to close the face and play on the leg side
stays in his crease and defends Elliott's tight length on a wicket to wicket line
a slower ball on a good length but on the pads, nudged behind square leg
moves towards the off side, gets down low and paddles to fine leg
that's just a gentle push down the ground but the timing is so good that Boult has a real chase on his hands from mid-on, he slides and drags the ball back just in time
defended on the back foot on the leg side
short of a length outside off, the batsman sways back and dabs late, placing the ball between a wide slip and backward point to third man
short of a length at the body, swatted through square leg
excellent timing! Leans forward and across and flicks a length ball off the pads all along the ground to the square leg boundary
driven to wide mid on for a single, Pakistan get to 250 in good time
nudged off the back foot towards midwicket for a single
poor line, on the pads, the batsman gets a bit of bat on it and it is enough to send the ball racing to the short fine leg boundary
played from the crease towards square leg

Has Rizwan been run out backing up too far? Sarfraz swatted the ball firmly back to the bowler and Elliott stuck his hand out and touched the ball before it crashed into the stumps at the non-striker's end. Rizwan was well out of his crease and when he slid his bat back in, it was in the air as the ball dislodged the bails
played off the back foot through the leg side
punched towards mid on
good length around off sump, defended on the back foot on the off side
stays back and plays another good length ball towards point
leans forward and pushes away from his body to play the full ball towards point
short of a length and that ball climbs on Wahab who gets on tip toe to play the ball down on the leg side
the leading edge lobs safely short of point! He was trying to turn that on the leg side but the ball got big on him. and then Guptill could have had run out had he hit at the bowler's end
punched to mid on and that is such a risky single, Boult missed after running in to field the ball or else Sarfraz was gone at the bowler's end
amazing placement! Swivels and pulls a short ball into the gap between long leg and deep backward square

gets down low to sweep a full ball but misses and is hit on the pad. There's an appeal for lbw but the umpire says not out. Think the impact was outside off sump. NZ decide not to review. Might have hit glove too
driven to long on for a single
gets behind the line of a good length ball and defends
dabbed off the back foot to backward point, there's a direct hit at the batsman's end but Sarfraz is safe
stays back and dabs the fullish ball towards short third man, several yells between the batsmen but they don't run in the end. Sarfraz was trying to keep the strike
good length on off, Wahab gets on the front foot and defends competently to cover, he is a capable lower-order bat
nudged off the back foot towards point, Wahab gets sent back by Sarfraz, edgy stuff
short of a length angling into the body at 144 kph, tucked off the hips through square leg
143 kph and homing on to the boot, Sarfraz jams his bat down on it in the nick of time, that would have been painful otherwise
stays back and steers the short of a length ball to third man
Wahab mows across the line and pulls hard, the short ball pings off the top edge and nearly carries over the boundary behind the keeper
played from the crease towards cover
backs away towards leg to make a bit off room and drives inside out to deep cover
a full ball outside off, played to point
wide line outside off, he reaches for it and plays to point
comes into Sarfraz from around the wicket, he dabs it close on the off side, behind point for a single
Wahab clears his front foot and swipes at a short of a length ball outside off, he was aiming over point but made no contact

whoa! He steps out of his crease and towards the off side to swat a short of a length ball towards square leg, the ball gets big on him and thuds off his body on to the lower part of the grille of his helmet
played towards point
stays back and dabs a good length ball with an open face to third man
short of a length and pretty straight, Wahab stays back and plays the ball down towards point
another top edge and another boundary! Wahab backs away towards leg and just pulls hard at the short delivery, the ball absolutely flies off that edge over the keeper and nearly went for six
backs away towards leg and then adjusts to swipe at a full ball right on the stumps, hits it towards cover
that carried to Anderson's left but it was such a hard chance. Sarfraz backed away towards leg and drove hard and straight, he didn't time it well but it was still travelling

Guptill is catching everything today! This time Wahab's pull against the short ball does not go over the keeper, it swirls in the air in the direction of midwicket and when it descends Guptill's safe hands are ready and waiting. That's his fourth catch
too wide outside off, Sarfraz does not play a shot
dabbed with soft hands close on the off side for a single
jumps up on his toes to play a short ball down on the leg side, Sarfraz calls Amir through
banged in short and that delivery from around the wicket follows the right-hander as he sways away from the line and tries to upper cut over the keeper
nudged off the pads through square leg for a single
dabs the ball off the back foot to third man for a single
151 kph that was! The ball was a blur as it flashed past Amir's swishing bat outside off stump, he went hard at that shot and was beaten

inside edge and caught behind! Maybe it was the pace of that previous ball but Amir was stuck in his crease as he poked tentatively at a good length delivery that sped through just outside off. It was the faintest of edges and an easy take for Ronchi
Rahat Ali gets beaten by a fast one on a good length outside off
another caught behind! Milne's line and length at that speed is just too good for the tail. Rahat is rooted to his crease as he pushes away from his body and nicks to Ronchi
that nearly bowled him! Milne takes a tumble in his follow through after the full ball beats the inside edge and just misses off stump
short ball angling into the body and Sarfraz swivels and pulls hard, beating Santner to his right at deep backward square leg
lower ball, Sarfraz backs away toward leg and cuts from middle stump line, he can't beat point
he calls for two, two, two as he cuts the full ball from middle stump to deep point, but there's no two there and Irfan is on strike
Boult targets the stumps with a full and straight ball, Irfan is good enough to keep it out, defending on the off side
nearly in the blockhole, but not quite, Irfan plays the ball towards point
fires the ball down leg side, looking for the yorker is Boult
good length on off and middle, Irfan defends watchfully on the off side to give the strike back to Sarfraz
moves forward and across to push towards wide mid on and Sarfraz doesn't take the single on offer
wait wait, yells Sarfraz to the advancing Irfan, sending him back. Sarfraz had moved across to whip the ball off his pads to long leg, he would not have been able to come back for two

well it's all over now, Pakistan don't even make 300. Sarfraz tries to pull a fast short ball and he ended up top edging it high in the air and to Ronchi, who takes his third catch off the speedy Milne.

inn2.comm: good length on middle and off, Guptill moves forward and defends on the off side towards point
good length and straight, Guptill stays back and defends on the off side
short and wide outside off, 132 kph, it sits up for Guptill who frees his arms and cuts hard, he hit it in the air through point
a fuller ball down leg side from over the wicket, Guptill can't connect as he moves across to glance
stays in his crease and defends a good length delivery back down the pitch
stays back and nudges a good length ball off his pads towards square leg
sprays the ball wide outside off, Guptil chases it with a powerful slash but can't reach it
short of a length pitching outside leg stump, the bounce is into Guptill's ribs and he fends it down on the leg side

McCullum's fallen first ball on his comeback! Amir bounced him from over the wicket and McCullum did not hold back, he hooked straightaway, but the ball went off the high part of the bat towards long leg where Irfan ran to his left to complete a sharp catch, he took that on the run
wide outside the off stump, Guptill chases again and bottom edges into the ground to the keeper
a full ball hits the pads after Guptill misses the flick, that pitched outside leg and swung back in a touch after angling across
short of a length outside off, Guptill hangs back and opens the face to steer behind point
strays wide down leg side, Amir is getting the ball to bend into the right-hander after angling across, but that line was outside leg and another wide
slants it wide outside off stump this time, Williamson lets it go
good length just outside off, defended off the back foot towards point
good length around off, Irfan's line and bounce denying Guptill width and space to free his arms, he defends on the off side
Guptill makes his own room! He moves forward and outside leg and frees his arms with power, slamming the ball flat towards the long off boundary
short of a length with a slant away from Guptill, who stays back and is beaten while trying to steer to third man
clears his front foot and slogs wildly across the line at a short of a length ball, he misses this tme
short ball, swivels and pulls to Malik at deep square leg
Williamson gets on tip toe to punch a length ball smoothly towards cover point where Babar dives to his left and fields
Guptill is hit on the top of the pad by a skiddy short of a length ball that pitches outside leg and cramps him for room as he tries to turn the ball though square leg
goes back and across to defend a short of a length ball on the leg side
an appeal for lbw as Guptill stays in his crease and swipes across the line at a full ball that crashes into the bottom of the pad, that swung into the right-hander too but was missing leg stump
Guptill clears his front foot and slogs, mis-timing it to mid-on, Amir is hurrying Guptill into his shots here, superb bowling
a full ball outside off, Guptill cuts it behind point and just wide enough of third man to come back for two
139 kph, a quick bouncer and Guptil sways out of the way
good length on a leg and middle line, Williamson stays back and defends
short of a length but there's width outside off, Williamson moves back and across and cuts the ball through the gap at cover point, got on top of the bounce so well
Irfan goes around the wicket and strays down leg side, Williamson glances but the ball goes off the thigh and beats the diving Sarfraz to his left
defended on the back foot on the off side

Williamson moves back and across again, this time to a short of a length ball that angles into him from around the wicket, and then he rolls his wrists to pull the ball along the ground for the third boundary in the over
defended from the crease with a straight bat
good length pitching around off and angling away from the right-hander from over the wicket, Guptill just wants to smash it and he plays a big cover drive but misses
the length is a bit shorter but the line the same - angling across the right-hander - Guptill stays back and plays a swishy cut and is beaten again
the bouncer! 140 kph, Guptill is cramped for room as he hooks but the boundaries here are small and Irfan is in the circle at short fine leg, the top edge carries over the fine leg boundary
the slower ball just outside off, played into the off side
good length outside off, this time Guptill stays balanced in his crease and leans into a controlled punch, the ball beats the diving fielder in the infield at cover

no shot offered and Amir roars an appeal for lbw! Pakistan will review the not-out decision. Williamson shouldered arms to an inswinger and it struck him flush on the knee roll. That was missing off stump though, by a long way
good length outside off, Guptill shoulders arms
played off the front foot into the covers

oh Guptill! What a blow that is. He clears his front foot outside leg stump, stays balanced, and swings through the line with a full flow of those long arms, he slams the full ball clean over the sightscreen
short of a length outside off, Guptill even lets it go this time, not swinging at everything anymore
short of a length and straight, Guptill stays in his crease an defends
gets behind the line of a good length ball and defends with a straight bat
a full ball slanting wide outside off, Williamson leans forward and lets it go
that's a fuller length and a closer line to off stump, Williamson still lets it go
good length but a little wider this time, Williamson stays back and cuts but is beaten
a similar ball to the previous one but Williamson lets it go this time
moves back and across to dab a good length ball to third man
short of a length and skiddy, rushes on to Guptill who has no time to connect with the pull shot, Amir has bowled superbly today
good length just outside off, Williamson presses forward and drives to cover
glanced off the hips towards long leg
stays back to a good length ball around off stump, defended on the off side
backs away outside leg stump and slugs a good length ball hard into the pitch, it bounces over the bowler to mid on
begins to push away from his body at a short of a length ball close outside off but checks his shot to let the ball pass

a half-volley around off stump, a poor end to a tight over, Williamson moved forward and presents a classic straight bat as he drives the ball along the ground past the bowler. Mid off had no chance. Williamson is by far my favourite batsman to watch in international cricket at present
hits a good length from over the wicket outside off and seams sharply away from Guptill as he prods from his crease and is beaten, Amir has troubled him a lot today
dabbed with soft hands towards mid off for a single
good length outside off, slanting away from Williamson who watchfully lets it go
moves back and across to defend a good length ball on the leg side, takes one hand off the bat as he does so
this time he's beaten! Williamson pushes forward and towards the off at a good length ball that seams away from him just outside off, he was trying to steer to third man

how good is Amir today? This one is a beauty. The length was fuller and after it slants across the right-hander from over the wicket it bends back in to beat Williamson's inside edge on the front foot drive. Williamson is good, but Amir was better that ball
Guptill swipes at a good length ball and chops it into the ground towards cover
how has that gone to the fine leg boundary? Guptill pushed forward to defend and the ball went between his legs off the inside edge and fine leg had no chance
stays back and defends the ball towards cover
gets behind the line of a good length ball and defends with a straight bat
punched off the back foot into the covers for a quick single and they take an overthrow too at the striker's end, the first single was a tight call
no room to play a forceful shot, played off the back foot on the off side
worked off the pads to fine leg for a single
short of a length at the body, that was measured at 123 kph but it looked faster, Guptill defends awkwardly on the off side, that hit his gloves hard
short of a length and straight, Guptill dabs the ball close on the off side and reaches the non-striker's end quickly enough to beat the direct hit from the fielder running in from point
turned off the hips to fine leg for a single
bouncer, but it is too high, that's a wide
once again Guptill calls for the single after dabbing the ball close on the off side, but Williamson sees the fielder at point is quicker to get to the ball this time and he sends Guptill back fast
stays back and defends a short of a length ball on the off side, towards cover
142 kph to start with, short of a length on a good line, Williamson is a bit late on the shot and he ends up swatting it towards mid off
stays back and defends a good length ball on the off side
145 kph, short of a length on a tight line just outside off from over the wicket, Williamson defends to short cover from his crease
moves back and across and punches a good length ball from outside off to mid-off, Wahab consistently over 140kph
stays back and punches a short of a length ball through cover
well that isn't the end of the over, Wahab bangs the ball in short of a length down leg side at 147 kph, a magnificent dive to his left from Sarfraz saves four wides
good length around off, defended on the back foot on the off side
Williamson pushes forward to defend a good length ball that bounces and slants across him from over the wicket and he is beaten
and he can do that too! Gets on to the front foot to a length ball and swings hard across the line, hitting the ball on the up with perfect balance clean over the deep midwicket boundary
Irfan losses his line and bowls too wide outside off
short of a length outside off, Williamson chases it with the cut but is beaten
checks his shot as he begins to push at a fuller ball outside off, more of a play and miss than a leave
and again, Irfan has troubled Williamson when he gets his length right around off stump, Willaimson is rooted to the crease as he prods outside off and is beaten
Williamson counter punches by moving outside off stump, inside his crease, and pulling a short of a length ball from outside off to the backward square leg boundary. A classy riposte
pushed off the front foot to wide mid on for a single
Williamson moves back and across to turn the ball through square leg but gets hit on the thigh as the ball comes back at him
stays back and defends on the off side
a fuller ball just outside off at 143 kph, defended on the front foot
short of a length at the body, defended close on the leg side off the back foot
he's timed that poorly but just well enough to clear the head of the fielder at mid-off, Williamson tried to loft through the line but the length was not full enough
Guptill slogs hard at a good length ball and hits it towards the bowler, Rahat takes pace off the shot and mid on does the est
Guptill half edges half steers a good length ball from outside off stump past first slip, Wahab runs quickly to his left on the third man boundary and slides to a save the four
width outside off to free the arms and Guptill stands tall inside his crease and slaps it over cover
short of a length and straight, no room his time and Guptill is hurried for time as he jumps back to defend
he's drilled that so hard down the ground for four! It was the slower one and a bit too full, Guptill met it on the front foot and drove it hard
strays down leg side with a full ball, Rahat is lucky Guptill did not make contact with his try at glancing the ball off the pads
Guptill has not been fluent today but he has battled through some testing bowling to get to his half-century, off only 54 balls. He gets there with a dab off the front foot towards midwicket

short of a length at the rib cage, Guptill jumps inside the line and fends it off his body past the keeper to the fine leg boundary. Did Wahab bowl that line and length because Guptill was getting his hand treated?
played through point for a single
Williamson moves smoothly back and across towards the off side to pull the ball down along the ground to long leg, Irfan moves to his left and gets down very low quickly to save the four
defended on the off side, Williamson begins to run but gets sent back
nudged off the hips through square leg, Pakistan need to find a way to put some dot balls together
Williamson also gets inside the line to a short of a length ball and glances it off his ribs past the keeper for the second four in the over to fine leg
good length just outside off, defended from the crease on the off side
Guptil jumps back and drives through cover as the drizzle continues to fall at Eden Park
there's also some sunshine along with the rain as Williamson stays in his crease and steers the ball to third man
good length outside off, defended on the off side
Guptill moves forward and across to a fuller ball slanting across him and drives through cover
Williamson stays back and drives a length ball through point
driven to long on for a single to bring up the 100 partnership
leans forward and turns the ball off his pads towards short fine leg
gets down low to nail the sweep shot, hitting it hard and along the ground and too well for Irfan to stop on the long leg boundary, he dived but did not get close to the ball
another powerful sweep, but straighter to the fielder at long leg, Babar Azam has been put there now
steps out of his crease and defends once he doesn't get to the pitch of the ball
goes back to pull and the ball falls a few yards short of Rizwan running in front deep midwicket, that was a short ball from Malik
driven hard and straight and right at the bowler, more a case of ball hitting the boot than boot stopping the ball
cuts off the back foot but mis-times the shot to point
cuts off the back foot but can't beat point
a full ball on a wicket to wicket line, Williamson chips the ball wide of and over the man at mid-on, the ball falls safely in the outfield
steered off the back foot to third man
pushes away from the body and gets a thick edge to third man for a single
Guptill is sweeping well today, gets down low on one knee and nails it again from outside leg stump, pressure on the bowler
Malik pitches outside leg and this time Guptill gets a little top edge towards short fine leg when he tries to sweep
punched back towards the bowler, Guptill hurries back into his crease
worked off the pads to short fine leg where Rahat can't get to the ball in time to cut off the single
played off the pads through square leg
once again he goes back to pick Malik off the pads behind square leg, no trouble whatsoever
and Williamson welcomes him with a firm drive off the front foot, he moved forward to hit that in the air but wide of Wahab's outstretched left hand, mid-off had no chance to his right
played off the back foot towards point, Wahab is bowling around the wicket angling the ball into the right-hander
steered to third man for a single
stays back and punches a short of a length ball through cover point
good length angling into the right-hander, defended on the front foot, the rain is the heaviest it has been today
and the rain has eased off just like that, Williamson gets to his half-century by whipping a length ball with the angle into him off his pads to the fine leg boundary
starts with a short ball outside off which Guptill simply smears off the front foot to the long off boundary
another short ball, the ball can't be easy to grip at all now, Guptil slaps it off the front foot to deep cover
nearly pulled it back to the bowler! Williamson rocked back to pull but mis-timed it
cut off the back foot to deep point, no turn at all and too short
played off the back foot towards cover point
steps out and drives the ball to long on for a single
a full ball wide outside off, Williamson hits the cover drive well but straight to the fielder
steered off the back foot to third man for a single
the short ball flies high over the batsman's head
stays back and plays with an open face towards backward point
short of a length and straight from over the wicket, 135kph, Guptill moves back and across to defend
slapped off the back foot after moving towards the off side for a single to deep cover
moves in his crease outside off stump to whip the ball off his hips through square leg
steps out and then has to reach for a wide one outside off and cut, he hits it with the toe of the bat and places it between short third man and backward point
steps out more this time to get to the pitch of the ball and drive to wide long off
steps out of his crease and drives the ball in the air but to the left of Azhar, who gets fingertips on a tough chance as it goes towards mid off
punched off the back foot to mid off
swept towards deep square leg for a single
defended from the crease on the leg side
played towards wide mid-on for a single, the fielder has to come in from the deep to get that
short of a length outside off, the batsman lets it go

that's hurt Williamson, he moved back and across to pull and swiveled too early to play the shot, it hit him on the back of the arm and he steps away to shake it off, that was the slower ball at 126 kph
tries to dab the ball with the angle across him to third man but can't make contact
shot! He moves forward and towards the off, to meet the ball with the angle across him from over the wicket, and then he frees his arms to play a flowing lofted drive clean over the bowler's head
moves back and across to glance off his hips to fine leg but can't connect
whoops! He's top edged it but the ball has fallen safely behind point, Guptill wound up and swung hard, looking to hit down the ground

he's been caught this time! Guptill tries to repeat the shot, clearing his front foot and swinging hard at a full ball, trying to hit down the ground, he ends up slicing it as the bat turns in his hand, an easy catch to point. Threw away his wicket there really
gets on to the front foot and defends on the leg side
moves across his crease, gets down on one knee and sweeps behind square leg
defended on the back foot to the bowler
played to long on for one more

short of a length outside off, cut off the back foot behind point and they race back for the second, Sarfraz collected the throw in front of the stumps, no idea why he wasn't behind the stumps because the batsman was still a long way out
played to midwicket, no run this time
played off the back foot towards cover point
that's too close to him to run down to third man and Williamson ends up bottom edging it into the ground
short of a length, he doesn't have much room but he still manages to pull it off the front foot with perfect balance to the deep midwicket boundary
and this goes all the way! Williamson moves forward to a full ball angling across him and plays the lofted drive through the line, clearing the long off boundary
a full ball, driven on the front foot to long on
reaches out for a wide one outside off and gets beaten while trying to cut

would you believe it? Azhar with his part-time legspin has got both set batsmen out! Williamson stepped out to the bowler but Azhar saw him coming and shortened the length, ripping the legbreak past Williamson, who was all at sea after not getting to the pitch of the ball. He barely made an attempt to get back as Sarfraz uprooted the stump, he was so far out
strides forward to a full ball and opens the face to steer the ball towards short third man, Azhar isn't pleased the single is conceded
bowled flatter and straighter, Nicholls defends to the bowler on the front foot
pitches just outside off and spins back into the left-hander, Nicholls goes back and taps the ball in front of point for a single
137 kph, good length and line, played to mid on
width outside off, Nicholls cuts hard off the back foot but can't beat point
stays in his crease and taps a good length ball coming into him with the angle towards midwicket
moves forward and dabs the ball with soft hands towards midwicket for another single
punched fluently off the front foot, stopped by the fielder moving to his right at cover
a full ball, nearly in the blockhole, Nicholls stays in his crease and plays the ball to mid off
gets on the front foot and opens the face to steer a legbreak to short third man
a flighted delivery outside off, driven on the front foot to cover
beats him in the flight as he pushes forward to defend and the legbreak spins and bounces past the outside edge
goes back and hits the shorter and flatter ball through cover point
defended from the crease on the leg side
that's a wide down leg side
bowled fuller and straighter, driven on the front foot to long on
Sarfraz had to jump up to collect that ball above his head, that's a wide for height

lbw! Amir follows the bouncer with a fuller and skiddy ball angling into the left-hander Nicholls who moves forward and across and is beaten on the inside edge as he tries to flick. Proper sucker punch that was. Would have hit middle stump
Amir sends down another full and fast ball, moving into the left-hander, Anderson defends on the off side
short ball, Anderson stands tall and pulls to deep square leg
good length at 139 kph, angling past the off stump after Elliott shoulders arms
a full ball outside off, driven on the front foot through point
a full ball swings into the pads, Anderson turns it to fine leg where Irfan does well to move to his left and field
that's the googly and Anderson lets it go outside off
driven on the front foot to mid off
driven back to the bowler on the front foot
pushed off the front foot towards the bowler again
tossed up outside off, driven on the front foot to long off
moves forward again and pushes gently to mid off
a length ball outside off, punched from the crease to mid off where the fielder is deep
a full ball angling into the left-hander, clipped off the pads though midwicket
nudged off the pads towards square leg
turned off the pads with the angle into him towards square leg
short ball from over the wicket to the right-hander, Elliott pulls in the air but the ball falls well short of long leg
too straight to the left-hander this over, Anderson glances off his pads again to fine leg this time
clipped off the pads through square leg for a single, NZ get to 200
full outside off, driven off the front foot to long off
goes back and hits the ball into the covers
played off the back foot to square leg
shot! Steps out to get to the pitch of the ball and lofts it far over the long boundary at deep midwicket
strays down leg side with a flat and fast ball
really short but it sorts of skids on instead of sitting up, Anderson goes back and defends on the leg side
the slog sweep, good contact, Wahab runs to his right and dives to save the boundary, great effort from the fielderat deep backward square
defended back to the bowler
caught at point! Malik has one now! A really harmless ball, flat and short outside off. It was there to be cut and Elliott cut it straight to Babar at point, such a soft dismissal.
he gets going immediately, nudging the ball on the off side for a quick single
Anderson dabs the ball softly on the leg side but Sarfraz runs to it quickly to prevent the singled
defended on the front foot on the off side
good length outside off, Ronchi pushes forward and is beaten, that was 147 kph!
full and straight, pushed to mid on for a single, New Zealand taking a while to get going after the resumption
short of a length outside off, gets big on Anderson who sways away and lets it go
short of a length outside off, Anderson drags it with a flat bat, pulling towards long on, a bit of a collision between Wahab and Anderson at the non-striker's end
Wahab races towards midwicket to keep the nudge off the hips down to a single, top over from him, only three off it
short ball on a wicket to wicket line, Ronchi swivels to pull but the ball gets big on him and beats the bat
short of a length, with width this time, New Zealand finally make a move, Ronchi cutting late and behind point for four
cut late again, this time to third man for just the single
a good length just outside off stump, dabbed with soft hands close on the off side for a single
a top delivery, short of a length angling sharply across the batsman with steep bounce, Ronchi fends at it and is beaten, they appeal for caught behind but no glove there

short ball and Ronchi pulls, it goes in the air towards deep square leg where Hafeez does not come forward fast enough to convert the chance, he got hands to it as he dived forward but could not hold on. Had he run in quicker he would have got there easily
mis-times the slog across the line and drags the ball towards square leg
good length on a wicket to wicket line, Ronchi goes back and nudges to midwicket, not in the gap so no run
a fuller ball, on leg stump, so Ronchi can flick it off his pads towards long leg for a single
after three tight balls, Rahat bowls a bouncer that is a bit too high

caught behind! Surely? Bowden says not out! Snicko shows a faint edge too! Pakistan are unlucky at such a crucial time. Anderson tried to pull a short of a length ball off the front foot and got a thin edge through to Sarfraz. Pakistan had already used up their review
he rubs it in now! Getting on to the front foot to a length ball and slamming it over the bowler's head for a straight six

is that the game? The caught behind not given followed by two successive sixes, Anderson lofts the ball cleanly off the front foot, sending the ball far over long on. Rahat got too full with his lengths after that caught behind appeal

edged in the air and it falls safe between three fielders! Ronchi tried to turn it on the leg side and the top edge flew just beyond the circle at short third man. Third man, point and the keeper converged on the ball but it dropped between them
too full and too much width outside off, Anderson continues to make use of that let off, it's triggered something in him, he gets on to the front foot and drives to the long off boundary
he hits the pads with a skiddy ball but that was missing leg stump, they run a leg bye towards point
a full ball outside off, driven to short cover
picks up a full ball on the front foot and hits through the line, lofting the ball high in the air and far enough for the ball to fall in the stands beyond long on
pushed from the crease towards point for a single, New Zealand cruising now
backs away towards leg but is cramped for room by Wahab's short of a length on leg stump, Ronchi tries to cut but is rushed for time and bottom edges past his stumps to the keeper
the fast bouncer is slightly down leg side and that's a wide
good length and straight, Ronchi can afford the luxury of defending on the leg side
aims for the big drive through cover but gets beaten by the full ball angling away
short of a length ball and Ronchi jumps back and pulls to deep midwicket
the slower ball slightly down leg side, Anderson pulls too early and gets a bottom edge past the keeper behind square
bowled him! Wahab was full and straight, Ronchi cleared his front foot and swung hard across the line. A dirty slog. He missed and the ball crashed into the stumps at 146 kph. Too late for Pakistan?
another appeal for caught behind but this time it is only to try and distract the umpire from calling a wide down leg side, Anderson missed the leg glance but New Zealand get an extra
pushed from the crease towards cover point where the fielder fumbles to allow the single
a full ball on the pads, neatly clipped through leg side for a single

caught by Babar Azam running in from deep midwicket! Anderson was looking to level the scores with a mow over midwicket, but he had to drag the short ball from outside off stump, the bat turned in his hand and he sliced it high in the air
tries to drive outside off but misses
short of a length outside off, Santner slugs it towards long on with a flat bat
what a finish from Irfan! Sends down a speedy delivery across the right-hander and beats Milne's steer to third man

what a cracking drive from Santner, this young man is so talented! He backs away towards leg to a good length ball right on the stumps and drives with power through cover, terrific timing and placement
short of a length and straight, Santner stays in his crease and pulls but gets beaten
he's beaten again! After that cool drive, Santner has played two rash slogs across the line, he tries to pull again but misses the good length ball that speeds over the stumps
there it is! Santner clears his front foot and drives the full and straight ball between midwicket and mid-on to win the series 2-0 for New Zealand
